						               													<description>BOOMA is a roll &amp;amp; write solitaire game where you will have to manage the workforce to catch the giant snake BOOMA that is ravaging the colony on planet Gliese 3323 b.&amp;#10;You can build electrified walls or generators, create bait or just bomb BOOMA and its clones.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Round&amp;#10;Rounds are played in three phases:&amp;#10;- Commander turn&amp;#10;- BOOMA turn&amp;#10;- Advancement on the tracks&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During commander turn, perform these steps in order:&amp;#10;1. Roll commander dice&amp;#10;2. Assign values (drawing one of the available symbol on an area, writing the number showing the dice inside the drawing)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During BOOMA turn, perform these steps in order:&amp;#10;1. Roll BOOMA bonus dice and trigger the corresponding effect&amp;#10;2. Move BOOMA and its clone (usually to the adjacent &amp;#10;orthogonally area with the highest value)&amp;#10;3. Clone growth: If the strength of the clone is less than that of BOOMA, then add 1 to the strength of the clone&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note that BOOMA and its clone are represented by two dice showing the value of the current strength.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You win in case BOOMA and its clone no longer have the &amp;#10;possibility to move.&amp;#10;You lose as soon as the second city area is devastated.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
